La majoria de galetes són galetes de sessió que s'eliminen automàticament del vostre disc dur després de tancar la sessió (és a dir, després de tancar la sessió o el vostre navegador web).Algunes galetes permeten que els llocs web us identifiquin en tornar a la pàgina. Sense el fitxer de galetes, els llocs web freqüents, com ara <<BRAND>> us tractaran com a nou usuari cada cop que torneu a entrar. Només heu d'eliminar les galetes si rebeu un missatge dient que el vostre navegador no accepta les galetes.
Comproveu que el vostre navegador té les galetes activades.

Les galetes són petits fitxers col·locats al disc dur del vostre ordinador per ajudar-nos a proporcionar els nostres serveis. Les galetes són petits fitxers els quals <<BRAND>> i altres llocs web emmagatzemen al vostre ordinador, permeten que aquests llocs “recordin" les vostres preferències i fan que no hagueu d'introduir la vostra contrasenya tan freqüentment. La funció d'inscripció d'<<BRAND>> funciona amb galetes.

Els procediments per gestionar les galetes són específics per a cada navegador web. Les instruccions següents són per a navegadors web recomanats per <<BRAND>>. Per a més informació sobre com gestionar les galetes en altres servidors web o serveis en línia (Netscape, AOL, Opera), vegeu l'Ajuda en línia del vostre navegador web.
Per comprovar que les funcions <<BRAND>> (incloent-hi la suscripció) funcionen correctament:
Seleccioneu Safari al menú superior i seleccioneu Preferències.

O podeu limitar les galetes seleccionant Només de llocs cap a on navego (ajust per defecte).

Quines coses pot fer un venedor fraudulent?

  • Demanar que gireu diners a un compte internacional. El venedor pot demanar-vos que envieu pagaments a l'estranger o només acceptarà Western Union o altre servei de transferències electròniques (e-Gold).
  • Llistar una adreça diferent de l'adreça que apareix a la seva pàgina de detalls de l'article.
  • Recomanar un servei de pagament o plica no conegut.
  • No aclarir l'autenticitat dels articles que es venen.
  • No proporcionar un número de telèfon comprovable.
  • Intentar convèncer per no usar serveis de pagament que ofereixen protecció (serveis acceptats: Escrow.com & PayPal).
  • No contestar a trucades de telèfon ni correus.
  • Proporcionar excuses sobre el motiu de no rebre un article.
  • Vendre còpies sospitoses de música, software o vídeos.
  • Rebutjar proporcionar-vos un número de seguiment d'enviament.
  • Vendre un article popular molt car a un preu baix sospitós.
Torna amunt

Com puc evitar un frau?
A <>, creiem que comprar articles localment - on els podeu inspeccionar, conèixer al venedor i pagar en el moment de l'entrega - és la forma més segura de fer transaccions. Per a articles nacionals o internacionals, aconsellem adoptar les mesures següents per protegir-vos enfront venedors fraudulents: Torna amunt

  • Utilitzeu sempre el sistema <>
    • En comunicar-vos amb venedors a <> utilitzeu sempre l'enllaç "Contactar amb el venedor" de la pàgina de detalls de l'article. S'enviarà un correu el venedor amb la vostra adreça de correu electrònic i les transaccions es realitzaran amb el venedor directament mitjanant aquest sistema. D'aquesta forma, si detectem una activitat fraudulenta del venedor, tindrem la informació de contacte per contactar-vos i proporcionar-vos informació. Com que el nostre mercat sempre és lliure, no hi ha motiu per comunicar-se fora el sistema.

  • Coneixeu allò que esteu comprant
    • Abans de fer una oferta al venedor, feu-li preguntes per saber els detalls de l'article que està venent. Podeu enviar una nota de pre-venda al venedor i fer la vostra oferta quan realment vulgueu comprar l'article. També aconsellem comprovar els preus minoristes i altres preus per comparar-los. Recordeu que si el preu sembla massa bo per ser veritat, probablement ho sigui. En particular, aneu amb compte quan compreu articles d'alta tecnologia, especialment quan el preu es troba per sota del preu minorista. Alguns articles d'alta tecnologia, com ara pantalles planes, portàtils i telèfons mòbils, solen ser l'objectiu de timadors. En molts casos, cal preguntar el número de sèrie abans de fer el pagament.

  • Pregunteu el telèfon i l'adreça del venedor
    • Després de negociar el preu i d'haver decidit comprar l'article, pregunteu el número de telèfon del venedor i truqueu-lo per assegurar-vos que rep les trucades. Els venedors amb bones intencions solen proporcionar informació. D'altra banda, tenir un venedor que disposa de número de telèfon registrat permetrà fer un seguiment del venedor i hi haurà menys probabilitats de frau.

  • Useu una forma de pagament amb protecció antifrau
    • No us aconsellem enviar pagaments per transferència electrònica. Molts venedors fraudulents només accepten transferències electròniques, Money Gram o transferències bancàries perquè els compradors no puguin tornar a disposar dels diners i no es pugui fer un seguiment dels venedors. Si residiu als EE.UU. i pagueu per gir, us aconsellem usar un gir postal. Els girs postals es poden investigar mentre que els altres no.

    Hi ha moltes formes de pagament que proporcionen protecció per als comprador. Les targes de crèdit, els serveis de plica como ara Escrow.com, enviament C.O.D. i serveis de pagament en línia, ofereixen molta protecció.

  • Feu un seguiment de la vostra entrega
    • La majoria d'empreses de transport permeten que les persones puguin fer un seguiment dels seus enviaments mentre es troben en trànsit. Us aconsellem obtenir el número de seguiment del venedor per tal de poder supervisar el vostre article en trànsit. Assegureu-vos que coneixeu el transportista del venedor i tingueu en compte que existeixen empreses de transport falses al web que pretenen fer seguiments d'enviaments falsos.

    Si creieu que un venedor actua de forma fraudulenta, poseu-vos en contacte amb <> immediatament a: abuse@OLX.com. Torna amunt

El valor del xec sol superar el valor del vostre article i el comprador us demana que li feu una transferència per la diferència. No aconsellem fer girs de diners.
    • Recomanar un servei de pagament o plica no conegut.
    • Fer comandes grans que s'enviaran a països estrangers.
    • Dir que us pagaran la meitat del valor abans de rebre l'article i l'altra meitat després.
    • No proporcionar un número de telèfon comprovable.
    • Pagar amb una tarja de crèdit estrangera o xec bancari.

    Quin tipus de publicacions estan prohibides / no permeses a <> ?
    <> prohibeix la llista de venda d'articles il·legals segons qualsevol llei, estatut, regulació o normativa local, estatal, provincial, nacional o internacional. Els tipus de anuncis següents estan prohibits al lloc <>: Publicacions de qualsevol franquícia, piràmide, esquema, club de membres, màrqueting de multi nivell, acord de representants de distribució o vendes o altre oportunitat comercial que requereixi un pagament periòdic, contractació d'un altre membre, sub-distribuidor o sub-agent, o pagui comissions només (excepte per a anuncis que identifiquin clarament que la feina disponible paga comissions només i descrigui el producte o servei que es ven, cas en el qual es permetrà aquest tipus de publicació).

    Altres articles específicament prohibits són:

    • Begudes alcohòliques
    • Sang, fluids corporals i parts corporals
    • Eines de robament
    • Monedes o segells falsos
    • Productes falsos
    • Equips de vigilància electrònica
    • Articles embargats
    • Uniformes del govern, identificacions i llicències
    • Medicaments il·legals & Parafernàlia mèdica
    • Qualsevol tipus de producte o servei il·legal.
    • Materials perillosos
    • Jocs d'artifici, dispositius destructius i explosius
    • Documents d'identitat, informes financers personals & Informació personal (en qualsevol format, incloent-hi llistes de correu electrònic)
    • Articles que incitin o facilitin les activitats il·legals
    • Tiquets de loteria, participacions i màquines escurabutxaques
    • Material obscè i qualsevol tipus de pornografia
    • Qualsevol tipus de material ofensiu
    • Pesticides
    • Imatges o fotos que continguin despullaments frontals
    • Uniformes i & plaques de la policia i altres forces de seguretat
    • Dispositius i medicaments sota recepta
    • Articles retirats
    • Participacions i altres actius financers
    • Propietats robades
    • Productes de tabac
    • Cosmètics usats
    • Armes i articles relacionats (com ara armes de foc, peces d'armes i revistes, munició, fusells d'aire comprimit i escopetes de perdigons, granades lacrimògenes, defensa elèctrica, navalles de molles i armes d'arts marcials)

A <>, creiem que comprar els articles de forma local (de manera que els puguis veure, trobar-te amb el venedor i pagar en el moment de la recollida o entrega) és la forma més segura de fer una transacció. En el cas d'articles nacionals o internacionals, et recomanem que prenguis les mesures següents per protegir-te dels venedors fraudulents:
  • Utilitza sempre el sistema <>
    Quan et comuniquis amb els venedors de <> fes-ho sempre mitjançant l'enllaç "Respon a l'anunci" que trobaràs a la pàgina de detalls de l'article. Enviarem un correu electrònic al venedor amb la teva adreça de correu electrònic i totes les transaccions es duran a terme entre tu i el venedor directament a través del nostre sistema. D'aquesta manera, si rebem la notificació d'activitat fraudulenta per part d'un venedor, tindrem les teves dades per poder-nos posar-nos en contacte amb tu i oferir-te la informació. Com que la plataforma és totalment gratuïta no hi hauria d'haver cap incentiu per dur les comunicacions a un altre lloc .
  • Coneix el que compres
    Abans de fer una oferta a un venedor, fes preguntes per conèixer més el que estan venent. Pots enviar una nota de prevenda al venedor, i després fer la teva oferta quan et sentis còmode amb la compra de l'article. També et recomanem que comprovis els preus de venda a les botigues i els preus d'altres usuaris per poder-los comparar. Recorda, si el preu sembla massa barat per ser real, probablement no ho sigui. Sobretot cal anar amb compte a l'hora de comprar articles d'alta tecnologia, especialment quan els preus són molt per sota els preus de venda al detall. Alguns articles d'última generació, com televisors de pantalla plana, ordinadors portàtils i telèfons mòbils són objectius probables per part dels estafadors. En molts casos és recomanable demanar el número de sèrie abans d'enviar el pagament.
  • Demana l'adreça del venedor i el número de telèfon
    Quan hagis negociat el preu i hagis decidit comprar l'article, demana el número de telèfon del venedor per trucar-li a una hora aleatòria per assegurar-te que respon les trucades. Els venedors honestos t'oferiran aquesta informació. A més, si un venedor té un número de telèfon registrat, farà que el venedor sigui més fàcil de localitzar i menys probable que sigui un frau.
  • Utilitza un mètode de pagament amb protecció contra el frau
    Recomanem que NO paguis mitjançant transferència electrònica. Molts venedors fraudulents només accepten diners per mitjà de transferència bancària, Money Gram o transferència electrònica, perquè d'aquesta manera els compradors no poden recuperar els diners i els venedors no poden ser localitzats. Si estàs als Estats Units i has de pagar per gir bancari, et recomanem que facis un gir postal. Els girs postals poden ser investigats, mentre que la resta no.
    Hi ha moltes formes de pagament que ofereixen protecció per als compradors. Les targetes de crèdit, els serveis de plica, com Escrow.com, els enviaments contrareembors, i els serveis de pagament en línia, ofereixen diversos graus de protecció.
  • Fes un seguiment del teu enviament
    La majoria de companyies de transport permeten fer un seguiment de l'enviament mentre està en trànsit. T'aconsellem que demanis al venedor el número de seguiment, perquè puguis seguir el teu article durant l'enviament. Comprova que coneguis l'empresa de transport del venedor, i tingues present que hi ha empreses de transport falses a Internet, que pretenen fer un seguiment d'un enviament inexistent.
Si creus que un venedor actua de forma fraudulenta, posa't en contacte immediatament amb <> a <>Temes Legals<>.

Què solen fer els possibles compradors fraudulents?

• Demanar-te que els enviïs diners al seu compte.
  • El comprador ofereix un taló d'alt valor (però fals) a canvi de l'article en venda. El valor del taló sovint excedeix el preu de l'article i el comprador et demana que li giris la diferència mitjançant un servei de transferència de diners. Els bancs normalment paguen aquests talons i TU PASSES A SER RESPONSABLE SI EL TALÓ NO TÉ FONS. L'estafa sovint implica una tercera part (agent de missatgeria, soci comercial que deu diners al comprador, etc.). Et recomanem que no facis cap transferència a un comprador.
  • Et recomanen un servei de plica o de pagament desconeguts.
  • Posen grans quantitats de diners a un lloc de l'estranger.
  • Diuen que et pagaran la meitat dels diners abans de rebre l'article i la meitat restant després.
  • No et proporcionaran un número de telèfon que es pugui comprovar.
  • Pagaran amb una targeta de crèdit internacional o amb un taló.
Què solen fer els possibles venedors fraudulents?

• Et demanen que facis una transferència a un compte internacional. El venedor et demanarà que facis un pagament a l'estranger i només acceptarà Western Union o un altre servei de transferència (e-Gold).
  • Indicaran una adreça diferent de l'adreça que apareix a la pàgina de l'anunci.
  • Et recomanaran un servei de plica o pagament desconegut.
  • No seran explícits sobre l'autenticitat dels articles que venen.
  • No t'oferiran un número de telèfon que puguis comprovar.
  • Intentaran convèncer-te de no utilitzar serveis de pagament que ofereixin protecció (serveis fiables com ara Escrow.com i PayPal).
  • No respondran les teves trucades o correus electrònics de forma repetida.

What is the Auction listing type?
What is the Buy Now listing type?

In the Buy Now-style listings, sellers have the option to offer a Buy Now price that allows a buyer to get the item right away. It is a fixed price transaction and the seller must sell the item to the interested buyer at the specified Buy Now price.
What is the Classifieds listing type?
In the Classifieds-style listings, buyers will always contact the seller to negotiate, even if he/she puts a price.

  • Bitllets de loteria, Participacions en apostes i màquines escurabutxaques
  • Material obscè i qualsevol tipus de pornografia
  • Qualsevol tipus de material ofensiu
  • Pesticides
  • Fotos o imatges que continguin nus frontals
  • Plaques policials i d'altres forces de seguretat i uniformes
  • Medicaments i dispositius amb recepta mèdica
  • Objectes retirats del mercat
  • Accions i altres valors
  • Propietat robada
  • Productes tabaquers
  • Cosmètics utilitzats
  • Eines i articles relacionats (com ara armes de foc, parts i revistes d'armes de foc, munició, pistoles de balins i pèl·lets, gas lacrimogen, pistoles de mentida, navalles automàtiques i armes d'arts marcials).

About OLX

OLX means free local classifieds on a global level. OLX allows you to meet others, express yourself, trade products, find jobs, apartments, and much more!

We built OLX to improve on traditional classified sites, which are functional but missing key features to really deliver a proper public service to communities everywhere.
On OLX you can:

  • Easily design rich HTML listings
  • Control your selling, buying, and community activity in My OLX
  • Send or accept PayPal payments
  • Be assured of a spam-free experience
  • Promote your listings on other websites, like MySpace, Xanga, and Blogspot
  • Discuss listings with other interested users
  • Enjoy a website that has world-class speed
  • Search for items near you, wherever you live
  • Access our site from your mobile phone
  • View our site in your local language
OLX has a presence on six continents. The company was founded in March 2006 and is privately held.

New to askht.com


What is askht.com?
askht.com is the world's online marketplace for local buying, and selling, exchanging and communicating to other users. Back to top

Is askht.com FREE?
Yes, askht.com is 100% free! Back to top

Do I have to Register to use askht.com?
No. You can browse the site and post items in the Classified section without registration. Registration is necessary in order to post a buy now or auction type of ad you. Registration at askht.com is FREE and the process is very simple:

1. Click on "Register Now" and you will be asked to provide your basic contact information.
2. You are now Registered at askht.com!
3. askht.com will send a message with your login and password information to your e-mail address.

Once you have registered, you can manage your postings and personal information even easier through the 'My askht.com' section of the site. Back to top

What type of buying and selling formats does askht.com offer?
askht.com buying and selling formats make it easy for buyers and sellers to do transactions together. Each format has its own characteristics and advantages.

1. Classified: Under this format, buyers can always contact the seller to negotiate, even if he or she puts a price to the item.

2. Buy Now: This is a price fixed transaction, where the user must sell the item to the first interested buyer at the stated price.

3. Auction: Rated auction, where the seller must sell the item to the highest bidder. Back to top

How do I find an item at askht.com ?
You can Browse listings when you're not sure what you're looking for, or when you simply want to explore the range of items on askht.com or in a particular category. Click on Categories and Subcategories and if you find an item you're interested in, just click on the item title.

You can also Search for items when you are looking for a specific item that you can describe using a few words. In this case, simply go to the search box, enter a few words describing what you are looking for and click the "Search" button. A search results page of askht.com listings will be displayed. Review your search results pages and if you see something you're interested in, just click on the item title. Back to top

What is My askht.com?
With My askht.com, you can track and manage your askht.com buying, selling, listings, personal account, information, messages, favorites and more from one single, secure location. You must be a registered user to access most of the My askht.com features. Back to top

Postings


How do I post an item at askht.com ?
Click on the "Post a free ad" button. If you don't have an account and don't want to register yet, just choose the location, the category and subcategory, and you are ready to post your classified ad. You can also register for an askht.com account by providing your basic contact information. Immediately after this very fast and simple registration process is complete you are ready to post. If you already have an askht.com account, simply login and follow the process. You will be asked to select categories and subcategories to post your item at askht.com. Posting at askht.com is FREE. Back to top


How do I upload a picture?
During the posting process, you will find the instructions to upload pictures. You simply have to follow them. askht.com picture upload process is easy and you can upload up to 20 (twenty) pictures per posting. Lighter pictures will upload faster; ideally less than 200kb each. Uploading pictures to askht.com is FREE. Back to top


How do I edit a posting?
If you are a registered user, you can edit your postings through the "All Listings" option in the My askht.com section of the site. Please go to the item and click the "Edit Listing" button. Once you have made and approved the changes, they will take effect immediately. You can repeat this process any time you like. If you are not a registered user yet, you can also access the same features using the link enclosed in the confirmation email you receive each time you post an item on the site. Back to top


How long will my posting appear on askht.com?
Currently postings on askht.com appear for a maximum of 365 days. After that time, the posting will automatically expire and it will be removed. Back to top


How do I remove my posting?
If you are a registered user and your item sells or you simply decide to remove it, you can end your listing in the Active link within the 'All Listings' option in the My askht.com section of the site. Once you identify the item you can mark it as Sold or remove it from the listing by clicking in "Sold" or "Remove Listing" button. If you are not a registered user yet, you can also access the same features using the link enclosed in the confirmation email you receive upon posting an item on the site. Back to top


How do I save a posting to recall it later?
Go to the listing you are interested in and click the "Add to Favorites" button to keep track of it. Back to top


How do I add HTML to customize my postings?
Yes. You can use HTML-formatted listings by cutting-and-pasting the code into the Description box during the posting process. However, we do not allow HTML in the Title field. Back to top


Can I include personal contact information in my postings ?
Yes. You can include personal contact information in your postings, except for the title of the ad in the Personals category (no email address, phone number, skype or other messenger ID). Back to top


Classified


What is Classifieds?
In the Classifieds-style listings, buyers will always contact the seller to negotiate, even if he/she puts a price. Back to top


As a seller, how do I post an item?
Click on the "Post a free ad" button to post without registration. If you already have an askht.com account, please login first. If you don't have an account yet and want to have the benefits of this FREE process, please register for an askht.com account by providing your basic contact information. After registration process is complete you are ready to post. You will start by selecting categories and subcategories that your posting will appear in. You will be asked to provide pricing -optional in some Subcategories- and delivery information together with an item description of any length. Posting on askht.com is absolutely FREE. Back to top


As a buyer, how do I contact a seller?
If the seller is a registered askht.com user, click on the "Contact seller" button in the listing you are interested. Fill the form with your contact information including your e-mail and the message you would like to send to the seller and submit it. If the seller is anonymous, use the contact information provided in the listing to get in touch with him/her. Back to top


Buy Now


What is Buy Now ?
In the Buy Now-style listings, Sellers have the option to offer a Buy Now price that allows a buyer to get the item right away. It is a fixed price transaction and the seller must sell the item to the interested buyer at the specified Buy Now price. Back to top


As a seller, how do I post an item ?
If you already have an askht.com account, please login first. If you don't have an account yet and want to have the benefits of this FREE process please register for an askht.com account by providing your basic contact information, After registration process is complete you are ready to post. In the Category List select the Category and then Subcategory in which your posting will appear. Finally, click on the Buy Now link and complete the form. You will be asked to provide pricing and delivery information together with an item description of any length. Posting in askht.com is absolutely FREE. Back to top


As a buyer, how do I contact a seller?
First, search or browse to find an item you are interested in. If you already have an askht.com account, please login. If you are not registered and have a question about the item, simply fill in the form with your return email address and your question and we will forward your message to the seller. You can also register and after registration process is complete go to the item and decide whether you're willing to buy the item for the Buy Now price. Then click the "Buy Now" button and continue. You will see a Buy Now confirmation message. Back to top

Auction


What is Auction?
In the Auction-style listing sellers put items up for sale to the highest bidder. Back to top


As a seller, how do I post an item?
If you already have an askht.com account, please first login. If you don't have an account yet, please register for an askht.com account by providing your basic contact information. After registration process is complete you are ready to post. In the Category List select the "For Sale/Auctions" option and after that choose the Subcategory in which your posting will appear. Finally, click on the "Auction with optional Buy Now" link and fill out the form. You will be asked to provide pricing and delivery information together with an item description of any length. Posting in askht.com is absolutely FREE. Back to top


As a buyer, how do I contact a seller?
First, search or browse to find an item you are interested in. If you are not registered, simply fill in the form with your return email address and your question and we will forward your message to the seller. If you already have an askht.com account, please login. If you don't have an account yet and wish to have the benefits of it, please register for an askht.com account by providing your basic contact information. After registration process is complete you are ready to bid. Go to the Minimum bid box, enter your bid and click "Place Bid". In the following screen enter the maximum amount you would be willing to pay for the item and click submit. You will not be able to change (raise) your bid on this auction until you have been outbid by another bidder. Back to top


What is the Reserve Price?
Reserve price is the minimum price a seller is willing to accept for an item. The seller has no obligation to sell the item if the reserve price is not met. The buyer is not shown the reserve price, but only showed whether or not the reserve has been met. A winning bidder must meet or exceed the reserve price and must also have the highest bid. Back to top


How do I know if I have won the auction?
At the end of the auction, you'll receive an email from askht.com indicating whether you've won the item, with an explanation of next steps. Back to top


More Guidelines


What are the things that potentially fraudulent sellers do?

  • Ask you to wire money into on International account. Seller may ask you to send payment overseas and will only accept Western Union or another money transfer service (e-Gold).
  • List an address that is different from the address on their item detail page.
  • Recommend an unfamiliar escrow or payment service.
  • Not be up front about the authenticity of items for sale.
  • Will not provide you a verifiable telephone number.
  • Try to convince you not to use payment services which offer protection (accepted services are those like Escrow.com & PayPal).
  • Will repeatedly not answer phone calls or email.
  • Continuously provide excuses about why you haven't received an item.
  • Sell suspect copies of software, music, or videos.
  • Refuse to give you a working shipment tracking number.
  • Sell an expensive popular item at a suspiciously low price.
Back to top


What should I do if I suspect a fraudulent seller?
If you feel there is a posting on the site that is false or fraudulent, please contact us at abuse@OLX.com. Back to top


How can I avoid a fraud?
At askht.com, we believe that buying items locally - where you can inspect the item, meet the seller and pay at the time of pickup or delivery -- is the surest and safest way to transact. For National or International items, we strongly suggest taking the following measures to protect yourself from fraudulent sellers: Back to top

  • Use always askht.com system
    • When communicating with sellers on askht.com always do it using the "Contact Seller" link on the page that details the item. An email will be sent out to the seller with your email address and all transactions will be conducted between you and the seller directly via our system. This way, if we are notified of a seller's fraudulent activity, we will have your contact information to reach you and provide you with the information. Since our marketplace is always free, there should be little incentive to take communications off line.

  • Know what you are buying
    • Before making an offer to a seller, ask questions to learn more about what they are selling. You can send a seller a pre-sale note, and then make your offer when you are comfortable with purchasing the item. We also recommend checking retail prices and other members' prices for comparison purposes. Remember, if the price looks too good to be true, it probably is. In particular, be careful when purchasing high-tech goods, especially when prices are far below retail. Certain high-end items such as flat-panel displays, notebook computers, and cell phones are likely targets for scammers. In many cases, it's appropriate to ask for a serial number before sending payment.

  • Ask for sellers address and telephone number
    • Once you have negotiated the price and have decided to buy the item, ask for the seller's phone number and call him/her up at a random time to make sure he/she is receiving the calls. Honest sellers should be able to provide this information. Having a seller who has a registered telephone number at the other end, will make the seller more trackable and hence less likely to be a fraud.

  • Use a payment method with fraud protection
    • We highly advise AGAINST sending payment via wire transfer. Many fraudulent sellers only accept money by wire transfer, Money Gram, or bank transfer because buyers cannot get their money back and sellers cannot be tracked. If you are within the US and must pay by money order, we suggest using a postal money order. Postal money orders can be investigated, while other money orders cannot.

    There are many forms of payment that provide protection for buyers. Credit cards, escrow services such as Escrow.com, C.O.D. shipping, and online payment services, offer varying degrees of protection.

  • Track your shipment
    • Most major shipping companies allow people to track shipments while they are in transit. We recommended getting a tracking number from the seller, so you can monitor your item in transit. Make sure you are familiar with the seller's shipper, and be aware that there are fake shipping companies on the web which pretend to track a false shipment.

    If you feel a seller is acting fraudulently, please contact askht.com immediately at: abuse@OLX.com. Back to top


    What are the things that potentially fraudulent buyers do?

    • Ask you to wire money into their account.
    • Buyer offers high-value (but fake) cashier's check in exchange for your for sale item. The value of cashier's check often far exceeds your item and the buyer asks you to wire the balance via money transfer service. Banks will often cash these fake checks AND THEN HOLD YOU RESPONSIBLE WHEN THE CHECK FAILS TO CLEAR . Scam often involves a 3rd party (shipping agent, business associate owing buyer money). We would strongly discourage you from wiring money.
    • Recommend an unfamiliar escrow or payment service.
    • Place large orders to be sent to a foreign location.
    • Say they will pay you half of what's due before they receive the item, and half payment afterwards.
    • Will not provide you a verifiable telephone number.
    • Pay with an international credit card or cashier's check.
    Back to top


    What should I do if I suspect a fraudulent buyer?
    If you feel a buyer is acting fraudulently, please contact us at abuse@OLX.com. Back to top


    What kind of postings are forbidden / not allowed on askht.com ?
    askht.com prohibits the listing or sale of any items that are illegal, under any applicable law, statute, ordinance or regulation at local, state, provincial, national or international law. The following type of listings are prohibited on askht.com site: Postings of any franchise, pyramid scheme, "club membership", multi-level marketing, distributorship or sales representatives arrangement or other business opportunity which requires an up front of periodic payment, requires recruitment of other member, sub-distributors or sub-agents, or pays commissions only (except for postings that make clear that the available job pays commission only and clearly describes the product or service that the job seeker would be selling, in which case such postings may be permissible).

    Other items that are specifically prohibited include:

    • Alcoholic Beverages
    • Blood, Bodily Fluids and Body Parts
    • Burglary Tools
    • Counterfeit currency, stamps or coins
    • Counterfeit Products
    • Electronic Surveillance Equipment
    • Embargoed Goods
    • Government and Transit Uniforms, IDs and Licenses
    • Illegal Drugs & Drug Paraphernalia
    • All type of illegal services and products.
    • Hazardous Materials
    • Fireworks, Destructive Devices and Explosives
    • Identity Documents, Personal Financial Records & Personal Information (in any form, including mailing lists)
    • Items which encourage or facilitate illegal activity
